about.summary: Summarize geospatial raster datasets based on vector geometries.

name: rasterstats
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "0.11" %}

package:
    name: rasterstats
    version: {{ version }}

source:
    fn: rasterstats-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    url: https://github.com/perrygeo/python-rasterstats/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: 0de3487986cb43f19613c653c170091d42b6f460aa7f3270f1646955faf6d5dd

build:
    number: 0
    preserve_egg_dir: True
    script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
    build:
        - python
        - setuptools
    run:
        - python
        - shapely
        - numpy >=1.9
        - rasterio >=0.27
        - cligj >=0.4
        - fiona
        - simplejson
        - gdal 2.1.*

test:
    imports:
        - rasterstats
    commands:
        - rio zonalstats --help
        - rio pointquery --help
    requires:
        - coverage
        - pyshp >=1.1.4
        - pytest

about:
  home: https://github.com/perrygeo/python-raster-stats
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  summary: 'Summarize geospatial raster datasets based on vector geometries.'

extra:
    recipe-maintainers:
        - perrygeo
        - ocefpaf
